    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/468.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 52.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your telegraphic communication 217
                    of August 27 last, relative to the American Mining and Milling Company of
                    Guanajuato, I have the honor to inform you, so that the company in question be
                    advised, that the Foreign Office on the date of October 1st, has been pleased to
                    advise me that proper orders were issued to the collectors of taxes at
                    Guanajuato, that no new payment shall be made on their properties, including
                    Siglo XX, Dolores, Edwin E. Harriet, Corwin and Green, and those of the
                    Consolidated Mining and Milling Co., known as Meliza and Ana Maria.</p>
                <p>With assurances [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. M. Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
